/**
 * T-23 + T-24 + PR-2 ÔÇö Operario Management Integration Suite (PR-1 + PR-2).
 *
 * Covers PR-1 OP-* scenarios:
 *   OP-01, OP-02 (create happy path ÔÇö SYSTEM_ADMIN, TALENTO_HUMANO)
 *   OP-03 (dup documento ÔåÆ 409)
 *   OP-04 (bad supervisorId ÔåÆ 400)
 *   OP-05, OP-06 (missing required fields ÔåÆ 400)
 *   OP-07 (COORDINADOR ÔåÆ 403)
 *   OP-09 (no token ÔåÆ 401)
 *   OP-24 (deactivate active ÔåÆ 200)
 *   OP-25, OP-26 (list active/inactive filter)
 *   OP-27 (deactivate already-inactive ÔåÆ 409)
 *   OP-28 (reactivate ÔåÆ 200)
 *   OP-29 (reactivate already-active ÔåÆ 409)
 *   OP-30 (deactivate non-existent ÔåÆ 404)
 *   OP-32 (TALENTO_HUMANO can deactivate/reactivate)
 *   OP-35 (attendance history preserved after deactivation)
 *
 * Covers PR-2 OP-* scenarios:
 *   OP-10 (all-valid CSV ÔåÆ 200, all rows persisted)
 *   OP-11 (mixed CSV: dup documento + unknown supervisor ÔåÆ partial success)
 *   OP-12 (in-file dup documento ÔåÆ first occurrence wins)
 *   OP-13 (all-invalid CSV ÔåÆ imported:0, nothing persisted)
 *   OP-14 (empty CSV ÔåÆ 400)
 *   OP-15 (malformed CSV ÔåÆ 400)
 *   OP-16 (LIDER_OPERATIVO ÔåÆ 403)
 *   OP-17 (supervisor resolved by email ÔÇö supervisorId linkage)
 *
 * Fixture setup:
 *   - Seeded zones (Zona Urab├í for S1)
 *   - Supervisor S1 (SYSTEM_ADMIN actor for write ops)
 *   - Supervisor S2 (for OP-17 in PR-2; here just used to have two supervisors)
 *   - TALENTO_HUMANO user with DeviceSession
 *   - COORDINADOR user (for 403 test)
 *   - Operarios created per-test inside describe blocks
 *
 * Teardown: FK-safe order (Attendance ÔåÆ Novedad ÔåÆ Operario ÔåÆ Supervisor ÔåÆ DeviceSession ÔåÆ User)
 */

